# Intentionally minimal: when this file exists, npm uses it instead of
# .gitignore for pack inclusion. The `files` allowlist in package.json is
# the source of truth for what ships in the published tarball; this file
# just suppresses npm's .gitignore fallback so `files` entries like
# `frontend/dist/` (which IS gitignored, as a build artifact) actually
# make it into the published package.
#
# Add explicit excludes here only if `files` is too coarse to express the
# exclusion needed.

# Keep node_modules out of the tarball even if a `files` entry would have
# implicitly included it.
node_modules/
